Initiative.

178
00:08:36,419 --> 00:08:39,059
It’s mainly because labor costs in China

179
00:08:39,059 --> 00:08:41,010
are going up for other reasons,

180
00:08:41,010 --> 00:08:42,949
and multinational companies want to make stuff

181
00:08:42,949 --> 00:08:44,389
to where it’s cheapest.

182
00:08:44,389 --> 00:08:45,709
China’s Belt and Road Initiative

183
00:08:45,709 --> 00:08:48,620
doesn’t exactly aim to reduce labor costs.

184
00:08:48,620 --> 00:08:52,459
It mainly seeks to get cheap raw materials
from poor countries,

185
00:08:52,459 --> 00:08:55,249
then assemble those raw materials back in
China,

186
00:08:55,249 --> 00:08:56,980
and then sell those finished products

187
00:08:56,980 --> 00:08:58,329
to other Belt and Road countries.

188
00:08:58,329 --> 00:09:01,149
That’s the goal of the Belt and Road.

189
00:09:01,149 --> 00:09:04,709
Also to create debt traps that other countries
can fall into.

